        "Three families of threats keep coming back. SQL injection on older PrestaShop versions, which lets an attacker read or alter the database — your orders and your customers. Web-skimming, or \"card skimming\": a snippet of malicious JavaScript slipped into the checkout page that quietly copies card numbers as the customer types them, with nothing looking wrong. And WooCommerce/WordPress module or plugin flaws, where a single abandoned or poorly updated plugin opens the door to everything else.",
